  <div class="ct">
  
<p>My Dad grew up during the depression and says that after my grandfather lost his job they often only had broth and a slice of bread for dinner. &nbsp;He said that was common among the families in his neighborhood. &nbsp;Things improved a little once my grandfather got a job with the WPA. &nbsp;</p>
<p>When my dad graduated form high school in 1938 there were no jobs so he joined the navy and sent most of his pay to his parents to help them and his younger brothers get by. &nbsp;He survived Pearl Harbor and spent most of the war on a destroyer in the Pacific. &nbsp;When he got out he went to college on the GI Bill. That government program helped create the middle class that brought prosperity to many.</p>
<p>Despite what the Republicans want to believe, the facts demonstrate that government programs play an important role in the creation of prosperity.</p>

